nk" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rotary_International">Rotary Foundation Global Grant</a>)</p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intergovernmental_organization"><strong>International organizations</strong></a> like the <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations">United Nations</a> or <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Bank">World Bank</a></p></li></ul><h2>Who Can Apply?</h2><p>You don’t need to be a topper to apply — but most full scholarships are <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Competition"><strong>competitive</strong></a>, so you need to be a <strong>strong candidate</strong>. Basic eligibility includes:</p><ul><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academic_achievement">Academic performance</a></p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IELTS">English language proficiency tests</a> (IELTS/TOEFL)</p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extracurricular_activity">Extracurricular activities</a> or volunteering</p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leadership">Leadership skills</a></p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Letter_of_recommendation">Letters of recommendation</a></p></li></ul><h2>Where Can You Study with a Full Scholarship?</h2><p>You can study almost <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_student"><strong>anywhere in the world</strong></a> with a full scholarship. Some popular destinations include:</p><ul><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Education_in_the_United_States"><strong>United States</strong></a>: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fulbright_Program">Fulbright</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knight-Hennessy_Scholars">Stanford Knight-Hennessy</a>, Gates</p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Education_in_the_United_Kingdom"><strong>United Kingdom</strong></a>: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chevening_Scholarships">Chevening</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rhodes_Scholarship">Rhodes Scholarship</a>, Commonwealth</p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Education_in_Germany"><strong>Germany</strong></a>: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DAAD">DAAD</a></p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Education_in_Canada"><strong>Canada</strong></a>: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="rich-text-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vanier_Canada_Graduate_Scholarships">Vanier Canada Graduate Scholarships</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noope