ently studying abroad. Thousands of Indian and Pakistani students are enrolled in universities across countries like the United States, United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, Germany, and other parts of Europe. In the event of a war or military conflict, these students may face a wide range of issues including mental health challenges, immigration restrictions, financial difficulties, and academic disruptions. This detailed guide explores how a potential war between India and Pakistan could impact students living and studying overseas.

